Hollywood may be the movie mecca of the world, but did you know Babelsberg Film Studio outside of Berlin is actually the oldest large-scale film studio?&nbsp;
Plenty of famous names passed through this film studio after it opened its doors in 1912, and some even launched their international careers there, including legends such as Alfred Hitchcock and Billy Wilder.
But Babelsberg is by no means Germany’s only claim to fame in the film industry.

